* Analyzing triangle angle measures using supplementary angle relationships and algebraic solving.
* Creating constructions and making conjectures about resulting angle measures.
* Writing proof steps for segment congruence using given midpoint relationships.
* Explaining why theorems about congruent supplements and complements have multiple cases and writing proofs for the alternate cases.

